<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100881079174290></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100881079174290><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=100881079174290>RE: Hail Tebyen!</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=100881079174290#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=65444><span id= >Tebyen the Wise</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>200 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Dec 19th 8:13 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[1.90]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hehe, wise I may be, but attention I do not pay. Like Bakra says, you get 30 points to begin with, and max you can put into any one stat is 25. If I didn't explain it before, the reason I said to put points into wisdom is this will determin how much mana you have, more so in later levels. The reason I suggested agility is that the more points into agility, the higher your ac. Also consider putting those extra 5 into stregnth (harder hits, and you can carry more loot), charisma (merchents offer more and charge less), dex (learn weapon skills faster, but not really needed in later levels), int is not needed to a druid, stamina determines how long you can swim, jump, and your hp, if I think of anything else, I'll post it.<br>&nbsp;<br>Tebyen Trueheart(druid)<br>Frizza (enchanter)<br>Tebyene (ranger)<br>Proud member of Cold Comfort</td></tr>
